&gt; In Java, the return keyword returns a value from a method. The method will return the value immediately when the keyword is encountered. ***This means that the method will not execute any more statements beyond the return keyword, and any local variables created in the method will be discarded.***

So back to your case, you have the following code:
```java
@Override public View onCreateView(LayoutInflater inflater, @Nullable ViewGroup container, @Nullable Bundle savedInstanceState) { super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
